A horse has been rescued after it became trapped in a boggy patch of field.Mid and West Wales Fire Service crews were called to the scene in Libanus near Brecon, Powys, at noon on Sunday.A 20-year-old horse was stuck in around four feet (1.22m) of mud.One of the horseâ€™s rear legs had become stuck deep in the bog and the horse had become exhausted trying to free itself, the fire service said. 
Crews successfully rescued the horse using salvage sheets, a slide mat, rescue equipment and shovels.  The horse was then left in the care of its owner and veterinarians.
